sequenceDiagram
    %% Episode 3 - ACK/NACK/no-response reliability path
    %% Solid arrows represent direct calls or frame writes; notes call out policy gates.
    autonumber

    participant Core as FSM step() / DomainAction
    participant AM as ActuationManager
    participant Router as Command Router
    participant Policy as FrontHeadlampPolicy
    participant Actuator as front_headlamp_actuator
    participant Bus as CAN bus / Reader
    participant Disp as Ingress Dispatch
    participant Ctrl as VehicleController

    Core->>AM: RequestFrontHeadlampOn
    AM->>Router: ActuationCommand{session,sequence}
    Router->>Policy: on_command_sent(cmd)
    Router->>Actuator: forward cmd (CAN)
    Actuator->>Bus: write command frame

    alt ACK received
      Actuator->>Bus: ACK frame(kind ACK_ON, session, sequence)
      Bus->>Policy: on_response(payload)
      Note over Policy: Validate pending + correlation + direction
      Policy-->>Disp: Accept(PhysicalCarVocabulary::Confirmed)
      Disp->>Ctrl: submit_physical_car_event(Confirmed)
      Ctrl->>Core: FsmEvent::FrontHeadlampOnAck
    else NACK received
      Actuator->>Bus: NACK frame(kind NACK_ON, session, sequence)
      Bus->>Policy: on_response(payload)
      Note over Policy: Same checks; accepted as Rejected event
      Policy-->>Disp: Accept(PhysicalCarVocabulary::Rejected)
      Disp->>Ctrl: submit_physical_car_event(Rejected)
      Ctrl->>Core: FsmEvent::FrontHeadlampActuationIncomplete{NegativeAck}
    else No response window
      Note over Core: TimerTick loop advances ack wait
      Core->>Core: try_front_headlamp_ack_timeout()
      Core->>Core: recover to safe lighting state
      Core-->>Core: DomainAction::LogWarning("timed out")
    end
